        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 28 at 10:21AM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 1021 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
western League City, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pasadena, Pearland, League City, Texas City, Friendswood, La Porte,
Deer Park, Alvin, Dickinson, South Houston, La Marque, Santa Fe,
Seabrook, Webster, Hitchcock, Manvel, Kemah, Greater Hobby Area,
Clear Lake, and South Belt / Ellington.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
